{
  "texts": [
    "If a paper fine-tunes from a pretrained foundation model, we do not consider it to be using outof-distribution public data.",
    "In Table 1 above, any bullet with out-of-distribution either empirically evaluates the method under out-of-distribution public data or theoretically studies it.",
    "The 'theory' column indicates whether a characterization of the privacy-utility trade-off is provided.",
    "All DP papers, by default, have a theory for the privacy part, thus not separated categorized.",
    "If there is a large amount of public data available, it can be used to pretrain a model."
  ]
}